viewssld is an open source SSL decryption daemon for Snort and other network Intrusion Detection System (IDS).

== Requirements
* libpcap
* libssl
* libdssl you can download it here: https://github.com/downloads/plashchynski/viewssld/libdssl-2.1.1.tar.gz


== Download
You can download the latest viewssld version here: https://github.com/downloads/plashchynski/viewssld/viewssld-0.7.0.tar.bz2


== Installation and Usage
See http://resources.infosecinstitute.com/ssl-decryption/ for more details. Please note that libdssl is no longer available at atomiclabs svn archive so the libdssl download link in the article doesn't work. You can download libdssl here: https://github.com/downloads/plashchynski/viewssld/libdssl-2.1.1.tar.gz


== Support
Need some help? Feel free to create an issue https://github.com/plashchynski/viewssld/issues
